China's health ministry said Tuesday the country  of 1.2 billion had 1,361 known carriers of the AIDS virus, nearly a quarter of  whom were foreigners or people who had been abroad.
Those who have contracted Human Immune-deficiency Virus (HIV) comprise  1,106 mainland residents and 255 foreigners or foreign citizens of Chinese  origin, said the official Xinhua news agency, received here.
Among the 40 people who have developed full-blown Acquired Immune  Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), 22 have died, the health ministry said.
The government says it plans to launch a publicity campaign and pass new  legislation in a bid to curb the spread of AIDS.
